{"lemma":"أُبُلَّةٌ","slug":"أُبُلَّةٌ","root":"#.ب.ل","root_slug":"_-ب-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ب-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["name"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n70","n71","n72","n3281"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8F%D8%A8%D9%8F%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"name","gloss":"Ávila (a province of Castile and León, Spain; capital: Ávila)"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Ávila (a city in Ávila, Castile and León, Spain)"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʔaː.bi.la/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n70","headword_ar":"اُبْلَةٌ","root":"Abl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A blight, blast, taint,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K:) thus written by IAth, agreeably with the authority of Aboo-Moosà; (TA;) occurring in a trad., in which it is said that one should not sell dates until he is secure from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAubolapN","text_ar":"الاُبْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, TA;) but accord. to a commentary on the Nh, it is correctly written ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abalapN","text_ar":"اَبَلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.] (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["T","K"]},{"entry_id":"n71","headword_ar":"اـِبْلَةٌ","root":"Abl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Enmity; hostility."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kr, M, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n72","headword_ar":"اَبَلَةٌ","root":"Abl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Unwholesomeness and heaviness of food;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K;) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wabalapN","text_ar":"وَبَلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHadN","text_ar":"اَحَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHadN","text_ar":"وَحَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abalN","text_ar":"اَبَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) It is said in a trad. that this departs from every property for which the poor-rate has been paid. (S, M.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ubolapN","text_ar":"اُبْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An evil quality"},{"kind":"text","text":"of herbage or pasture. (AHn, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n$r","text_ar":"نشر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cause of harm"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"injury; evil; mischief."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A consequence"},{"kind":"text","text":"of an action, or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a claim which one seeks to obtain for an injury;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cause of blame"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispraise:"},{"kind":"text","text":"having these meanings in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino faEalota *aAka faqado xarajota mino A^abalatihi","text_ar":"اـِنْ فَعَلْتَ ذَاكَ فَقَدْ خَرَجْتَ مِنْ اَبَلَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If thou do that, thou wilt escape from its consequence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (T.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A fault, vice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Málik, T.) So in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA Ealayoka fiY","text_ar":"مَا عَلَيْكَ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA AlA^amori A^abalapN","text_ar":"هٰذَا الاَمْرِ اَبَلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not to be charged against thee, in this affair, any fault,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (T.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A crime; a sin; an unlawful action."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rancour, malevolence, malice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spite."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IB.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n3281","headword_ar":"اَبْلَهُ","root":"blh","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Heedless:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heedless of evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of his goodness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"simple, foolish,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of little sense, without discrimination:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weak in intellect:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) accord. to En-Nadr, (TA,) one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose evilness is dead,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that he is not cognizant of it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good in disposition; having little cognizance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"understanding, of subtilties;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having little skill therein:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose predominant quality is freedom of the bosom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mind, from evil affections;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and good opinion of men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"simple-hearted:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"naturally disposed to goodness, and therefore heedless of evil, not knowing it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heedless with respect to the present world and its people and their corruptness and malevolence, but intelligent and skilled in the law with respect to that which is commanded and that which is forbidden:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ah- mad Ibn-Hambal, TA:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balohaA='u","text_ar":"بَلْهَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb, K: *) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bulohN","text_ar":"بُلْهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bulahaA='u","text_ar":"بُلَهَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", a pl., [as though the sing. were"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baliyhN","text_ar":"بَلِيهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dull, stupid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wanting in intelligence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this is post-classical. (TA.) Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAb~N A^abolahu","text_ar":"شَابٌّ اَبْلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A youth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young man, who is heedless,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.], because of his inexperience in affairs: the epithet is applied to a youth in like manner as freedom from care, or thought, and like as insanity, are attributed to him. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayoru A^awolaAdinaA AlA^abolahu AlEaquwlu","text_ar":"خَيْرُ اَوْلَادِنَا الاَبْلَهُ العَقُولُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The best of our children is the heedless,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has much intelligence"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, Msb;) a saying of Ez-Zibrikán Ibn-Bedr; (S;) meaning such as, by reason of his bashfulness, is like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ablh","text_ar":"ابله"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) so that he feigns heedlessness, and passes over things, (Msb,) though he has much intelligence; (S;) or such as is thought to be stupid, but, when examined, is found to be [very] intelligent. (IAth, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eql","text_ar":"عقل"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akovaru A^aholi Aljan~api Albulohu","text_ar":"اَكْثَرُ اَهْلِ الجَنَّةِ البُلْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a trad., meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Most of the people of Paradise are the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buloh","text_ar":"بُلْه"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heedless,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,] with respect to the present world, because of their being little concerned thereby, while they are intelligent with respect to the world to come; (S;) or they are thus termed because they are heedless of their affairs in the present world, and unskilful in the management thereof, and busy themselves with their affairs relating to the world to come. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balohaA='u","text_ar":"بَلْهَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a woman,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Generous, strong-hearted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maziyrapN","text_ar":"مَزِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almariyrapu","text_ar":"المَرِيرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the copies of the K is a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almaziyrapu","text_ar":"المَزِيرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zAY","text_ar":"زاى"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA, [app. here meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bold,"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inexperienced in affairs, and simple,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unintelligent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.) ISh cites a poet as applying this epithet to a young girl with whom he had sported, and who acquainted him with her secrets, by reason of her inexperience, and want of cunning, not knowing what that implied against her. (TA.) ―         -b3-  Also, applied to a she-camel, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That does not take fright, and flee from a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of staidness,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":255},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heaviness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though she were stupid."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, A, K.) One does not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamalN A^abolahu","text_ar":"جَمَلٌ اَبْلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (ISh, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abaAbN A^abolahu","text_ar":"شَبَابٌ اَبْلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"delicate, youth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, A, K;) as though he who enjoys it were heedless of nocturnal accidents or calamities. (A, K.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayo$N A^abolahu","text_ar":"عَيْشٌ اَبْلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"delicate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plentiful and easy, life:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a life in which are few anxieties:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(CK:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a life in which are few griefs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sorrows."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bulahoniyapN","text_ar":"بُلَهْنِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","Msb","TK","T","S","ISh","A","CK"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}